    "That is, each list employed had a continuous distribution of (semantic) similarity among the new items and the studied ones.",
    "As for Experiment 1, participants were asked to study lists of words and then to perform a recognition task.",
    "We expected to replicate the results of Experiment 1 with participants' false recognition proportions for close new items to be significantly higher than those for far new items.",
